 to plot the answers on a graph you might assume the scatter-plot forms a bell curve: i.e. a lot of people guess close to the right answer. Not necessarily (See below). For sure, it\u2019s not required to. The average is also not popular opinion, that is the mode. In this case the average is the shared consensus we get when we honor our differences."), mdx("h2", null, "A Caveat: Averages Make for Poor KPIs."), mdx("p", null, "It would be a mistake to rely on an average as a KPI. To benefit from the \u201C", mdx("a", {
